Figure 6: Key spectral features in the NIRSpec prism data. a , The full NIRSpec prism spectrum of JF-z3 in the rest frame. Three key spectral features are highlighted in panels b , c , and d . b , Prominent Balmer/4000 Å break with a strength of B4200/3500= \(f_{
u}(4200\,	ext{\AA })/f_{
u}(3500\,	ext{\AA })=3.32\pm 0.10\) , where the wavelength ranges used to estimate \(f_{
u}(3500\,	ext{\AA })\) and \(f_{
u}(4200\,	ext{\AA })\) are shown with red lines. c , Molecular cyanogen absorption feature, i.e., the CN 1.1 \(\mu\) m edge. The spectrum has been normalized to the continuum blueward of the CN edge. He i and Pa \(\gamma\) emission lines are annotated. The wavelength range used to estimate the flux redward of the CN edge is denoted by the red line. d , [Fe ii ] and hydrogen Pa \( eta\) emission lines. Gaussian models for both lines are overlaid as red dashed lines. The Balmer/4000 Å break and CN 1.1 \(\mu\) m edge indicate the post-starburst nature of JF-z3; while the high line ratio of [Fe ii ]/Pa \( eta\) suggests the shock from ram pressure.

